    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nFloating window background color doesn't match terminal with `termguicolors`, `guibg=none`, and `winblend` > 0.\r\n\r\nTo see this, the terminal color has to be set to one that is neither white nor black.\r\n\r\nThis issue is not present when using `notermguicolors`.\r\n\r\nI noticed this when investigating an issue reported for a scrollbar plugin I wrote:\r\nhttps://github.com/dstein64/nvim-scrollview/issues/112\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nFirst change your terminal color to one that is neither white nor black.\r\n\r\n`nvim --clean`\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n\" Set termguicolors\r\n:set termguicolors\r\n\r\n\" Create a new tab\r\n:tabe\r\n\r\n\" Create a floating window\r\n:let opts = {\r\n      \\   'relative': 'editor',\r\n      \\   'width': 30,\r\n      \\   'height': 20,\r\n      \\   'col': 5,\r\n      \\   'row': 5,\r\n      \\   'zindex': 100,\r\n      \\   'border': 'single'\r\n      \\ }\r\n:let bufnr = nvim_create_buf(v:false, v:true)\r\n:let win = nvim_open_win(bufnr, 0, opts)\r\n\r\n\" Remove Normal's guibg and ctermbg, intended to match terminal background\r\n:highlight normal guibg=none ctermbg=none\r\n\r\n\" Set floating window highlight to Normal\r\n:call nvim_win_set_option(win, 'winhighlight', 'Normal:Normal')\r\n\r\n\" Set positive value for winblend\r\n:call nvim_win_set_option(win, 'winblend', 50)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n(expected behavior was generated by changing `set termguicolors` to `set notermguicolors` in the steps above)\r\n\r\n| Actual | Expected |\r\n| :-----:|:-------: |\r\n| ![actual](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/541289/d00460af-3f36-4f89-86f0-43072cd61a1d) | ![expected](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/541289/f4a4e5fc-1d7b-4274-9f39-d06b41417815) |\r\n\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.9.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nKubuntu 23.04\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nKonsole 22.12.3\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nappimage",
